# PZ Icons Tool

Use the `pzicons` CLI tool to convert SVG icons to PZ mod-ready PNG textures.

## Installation

```powershell
uv tool install C:\Users\onifent\Documents\projects\mod_utils\icons
```

## Converting Icons

```powershell
# Basic conversion (generates 16, 24, 32, 48, 64 px icons)
pzicons convert icon.svg

# With PZ-specific colors
pzicons convert checkmark.svg -c pz-green    # Level up, success
pzicons convert lock.svg -c pz-red           # Locked, damage

# Custom hex color
pzicons convert icon.svg -c "#4CAF50"

# Specific sizes only
pzicons convert icon.svg -s 32,64

# Custom output directory and filename
pzicons convert check.svg -o ./media/textures -n upgrade_complete -c pz-green

# Batch convert multiple SVGs
pzicons batch *.svg -c pz-green -o ./textures
```

## Output Location

Place generated PNGs in:
```
MySpatialRefuge/Contents/mods/myspatialrefuge/42.13/media/textures/
```

## Using in Lua Code

```lua
-- Load texture
local icon = getTexture("media/textures/checkbox_32x32.png")

-- Draw in UI panel render()
if icon then
    self:drawTextureScaledAspect(icon, x, y, 32, 32, 1, 1, 1, 1)
end

-- With color tint (r, g, b values 0-1)
self:drawTextureScaledAspect(icon, x, y, 32, 32, 1, 0.5, 1, 0.5)
```

## Named Colors

| Name | RGB | Use Case |
|------|-----|----------|
| `pz-green` | (137, 232, 148) | Level up, success, upgrades complete |
| `pz-red` | (255, 105, 97) | Damage, locked, unavailable |
| `pz-good` | (100, 200, 100) | Positive effects |
| `pz-bad` | (200, 100, 100) | Negative effects |
| `white` | (255, 255, 255) | For tinting in-game |

## Recommended Icon Sizes

| Size | Use |
|------|-----|
| 16x16 | Small badges, indicators |
| 24x24 | List items, small buttons |
| 32x32 | Standard icons, grid items |
| 48x48 | Large buttons, headers |
| 64x64 | Window icons, main elements |

## SVG Requirements

- Use **filled shapes** (not strokes) for best results
- Use **black/dark colors** - they'll be replaced with target color
- White/light backgrounds are automatically made transparent
- Recommended source: [Lucide](https://lucide.dev), [Heroicons](https://heroicons.com)

